HEADWORD: Scioptics
<hw>Sci*op"tics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The art or process
of exhibiting luminous images, especially those of external objects, in
a darkened room, by arrangements of lenses or mirrors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scioptric</ent>⟦br⟧
